.SH NAME
sync \- Synchronize cached writes to persistent storage
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B sync
[\fI\,OPTION\/\fR] [\fI\,FILE\/\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.\" Add any additional description here
.PP
Synchronize cached writes to persistent storage
.PP
If one or more files are specified, sync only them,
or their containing file systems.
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#sync-d'\fB\-d, \-\-data\fP\X'tty: link'
sync only file data, no unneeded metadata
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/manual/coreutils.html#sync-f'\fB\-f, \-\-file\-system\fP\X'tty: link'
sync the file systems that contain the files
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/sync#sync--help'\fB\-\-help\fP\X'tty: link'
display this help and exit
.TP
\X'tty: link https://www.gnu.org/software/coreutils/sync#sync--version'\fB\-\-version\fP\X'tty: link'
output version information and exit
.SH BUGS
